A lot of experiments were designed to investigate the features of the sensor and the data were shown in Fig. 4
                        . It was apparent that the calibration curve earned good linearity over the range of 0.002–0.06 μg mL−1 (R2 = 0.998). The limit of detection of BaP was 0.16 ng mL−1 based on 3σ/slope, where σ was the standard deviation of the blank signals (n = 15). Moreover, the parameters of this sensor were compared with the existed methods (Table 1
                        ). It is obvious that this method shows significant advantages in sensitivity, linear range and repeatability. These data exhibited this fluorescence sensor can be used to detect trace amounts of BaP in water solutions and have good prospects in sample application.
